  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;
Thank you for reaching out to us via the NHS Choices website and providing your constructive feedback.  It's good to know you feel you were treated wonderfully in ENT at Royal Preston and we shall certainly pass that on.

We're sorry to know that the experience was married by having to walk through smoke at the front entrance of a hospital. We do recognise this, and your suggestion of security staff/policing the area is certainly an option – but one that is fairly expensive to cover 24 hours per day.  It is likely that this would temporarily shift rather than reduce the number of smokers on site.

Our resources are committed to training our staff to assess all patients for their smoking status to ensure that we have the greatest opportunity to manage their withdrawal successfully. In doing this, we can significantly reduce the number of patients who feel the need to go outside to smoke. This is a sustainable and evidence based approach to reducing smoking and one that is supported by the National Institute for Health and Clinical Excellence.

We have also revised our prescribing guidance to ensure that we prescribe sufficient Nicotine Replacement Therapy – this is key to managing the withdrawal symptoms that leads to someone smoking whilst in hospital.

We recognise that this is unlikely to change the situation overnight, and for that we can only apologise and would like to reassure you that we are committed to improving this situation and the experience of all of our patients, relatives and visitors in the most effective and sustainable way.
&lt;/CommentText&gt;
